.TH SDLTIMER 1 "2026-06-08" "sdltimer 1.0" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
sdltimer \- countdown timer with SDL3 7-segment display
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B sdltimer
[\fIduration\fR]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B sdltimer
opens an SDL3 window and shows a big red 7-segment countdown.
It starts paused; press SPACE to begin.
.PP
The display shows MM:SS.  The colon blinks once per second while
counting.  Timer state is reflected in the window title.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.BR \-h ", " \-\-help
Show help and exit.
.TP
.BR \-v ", " \-\-version
Show version and exit.
.TP
.BI duration
Countdown duration.  Can be a plain number (seconds) or use
h/m/s suffixes.  Default is 300 (5 minutes).
.RS
.PP
Examples:
.RS
.nf
90      90 seconds
90s     90 seconds
5m      5 minutes
1h      1 hour
1h30m   1 hour 30 minutes
1h30m20s 1 hour 30 minutes 20 seconds
.RE
.RE
.SH CONTROLS
.TP
.B SPACE
Start or pause the countdown.
.TP
.B r
Reset the timer back to its initial duration.  Does nothing if the
timer hasn't been started yet.
.TP
.B ESC
Quit.
.SH STATES
.TP
Running
Bright red digits, blinking colon.
.TP
Paused
Dim amber digits, colon stays on.
.TP
Finished
Flashes red on and off every 500 ms.  Window title says FINISHED!.
.SH BUILD
.B sdltimer
depends on SDL3 (>= 3.2) and clibx.  Both should be discoverable
through pkg-config.  Just run
.B make
at the project root.
.SH FILES
.TP
.B /usr/local/bin/sdltimer
The binary (after install).
.TP
.B /usr/local/share/man/man1/sdltimer.1
This man page.
.SH BUGS
The 7-segment renderer uses integer math for segment positions, but
SDL_FRect expects floats.  On very small windows the segments may
look squished.
.PP
Report bugs to the author or just fix them yourself.
.SH AUTHOR
David Balishyan <davidbalishyan12@gmail.com>
